Description: Three joinig body sherds of grey ware black burnished pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe; light brown fabric and dark brown core with numerous mica and limestone inclusions; very worn black polish on exterior.
Curator's comments: According to Perkins (2007) p. 60 #235, sherd belongs to same vessel as 1924.1201.76.b-w, however,there is no evidence that sherd joins any other sherd (except 1924.1201,76,g). Also according to Perkins, sherds 1888,0601.643b-d probably also join those listed above.
Bibliographic references: Etruscan Bucchero / A Catalogue of Etruscan Bucchero in the British Museum (No. 235)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.152)
